The paper deals with the reconstruction of 3D shapes from sparse data, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The proposed method involves the use of statistical shape models (SSMs), which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.MM) and data analysis (cs.LG). The method also involves the use of a Gaussian Mixture Model (GMM), which is a common tool in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
